<item>
            <title>[LU-14161] conf-sanity/91 may fail due to rhashtable restart</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14161</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;according to rhashtable documentation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, you may miss objects if there are removals in between rhashtable_walk_stop and the next call to rhashtable_walk_start.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so the fix could be to restart the iteration from scratch using rhashtable_walk_exit() and rhashtable_walk_enter()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
